{"body": "\"it is relying on the undocumented return value of the predicate\"\r\n\r\nI'd almost say it's a failure of Ruby's predicate methods not to coerce to a boolean and instead presenting \"truthy\"/\"falsey\" values. These can be quite confusing from irb.\r\n\r\n+1 on coercing to true/false unless there's a legitimate performance concern which dictates otherwise. Returning nil and 0 is especially confusing considering that 0 is \"truthy\" in Ruby and false in most other languages.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4669330", "created_at": "2012-03-23T22:46:19Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5329#issuecomment-4669330", "updated_at": "2012-03-23T22:46:19Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5329, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tarcieri", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/4131d2f57a0db2a2b4d9a62bd389fd44?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbeb22fb694d513edcf5533cf006dfeae.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4131d2f57a0db2a2b4d9a62bd389fd44", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tarcieri", "type": "User", "id": 797, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tarcieri/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523819bdbd3543c15100e203"}, "id": 4669330, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5329"}
